the Island Way Pina Colada Sorbet with the homemade pineapple compote is the perfect combo 🍍these sorbets are my favorite- they’re creamy, delish & come in a real fruit shell 🙌🏼

recipe:
1 small pineapple
2 tbsp sugar
2-3 tbsp water
1 tsp agar agar 
Island Way Sorbet Pina Colada Sorbet

instructions:
slice your pineapple into chunks
heat up your pot
mix in the pineapple chunks, sugar, water and agar agar 
mix every few minutes 
let it cook for around 10 minutes until done, stirring every few minutes 
let it cool and scoop it onto the Island Way Sorbet pina colada sorbet

attn coffee lovers this one is for you 📣the combo of @islandwayusa heavenly coconut sorbet + this homemade coffee syrup shell will be your new fav!
here’s part 2 of our Sundae Scaries series! in this series we’re sharing fun toppings to complement Island Way’s fruit sorbet (that btw come in a real fruit shell 🙊)
recipe:
¼ cup coffee (I mixed 1 tbsp instant coffee with 3-4 tbsp water)
¼ cup coconut oil
3 tbsp sweetener
⅓ cup white chocolate chips
Island Way Sorbet Heavenly Coconut
 
instructions:
melt your coffee with the coconut oil and sweetener
let it mix together and reach a boil - keep stirring every so often
add in the white chocolate chips and mix in until well combined (let it reach a boil to a syrup consistency) it can take few minutes
place a spoonful of this coffee syrup onto the Island Way Coconut Sorbet
place in the freezer for 25 minutes to harden
enjoy!
